---
// AssuranceTiers.astro
// Graduated trust levels — software, TEE, VCAV
---

<section class="section section--alt reveal" id="assurance">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tiers">
      <h2 class="tiers__title">Assurance Tiers</h2>
      <dl class="tiers__grid">
        <div class="tier-card">
          <dt class="tier-card__term font-mono">Software lane — SELF_ASSERTED</dt>
          <dd class="tier-card__def">
            The relay operator can see your data — you trust them the way you trust any
            SaaS provider. The bounded channel is enforced structurally via schema validation
            and guardian policy. The receipt proves which contract, schema, and policy governed
            the session. It does not prove the relay ran the stated model or refrained from
            logging your input.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card">
          <dt class="tier-card__term font-mono">TEE lane — HARDWARE_ATTESTED</dt>
          <dd class="tier-card__def">
            Coordination runs inside an AMD SEV-SNP confidential VM. Hardware-encrypted memory
            excludes the operator from plaintext, even with root access. The receipt is bound
            to the measured execution environment via attestation hash and transcript hash.
            Validated on GCP N2D instances (AMD Milan).
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-card">
          <dt class="tier-card__term font-mono">VCAV — highest assurance</dt>
          <dd class="tier-card__def">
            Local models, hardware attestation, and side-channel hardening shrink the trust
            boundary to the sealed VM itself. A dedicated orchestrator enforces information
            flow control and privacy budgets. Same bounded-disclosure principle, strongest
            guarantees.
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .tiers {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .tiers__title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .tiers__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .tier-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-bg-panel);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .tier-card__term {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .tier-card__def {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
